race.comment: RUNLIKENENCRYPTION (12) rattled the bar in town a few times last prep. Looks capable of winning one in the big spoke and confirmed that by again running well and just missing out when resuming on the Heath. Now she finds her race. Not a great deal on her plate here and if she takes a nice step forward on the return she's the one to beat. Back to the short course worked for BLACKBERRY BOMB (8) last time so the 1000m can set up nicely for her. MR MAGNUS (6) needs things to fall in his lap a bit and his overall record tells you a bit about that but he's got the talent if stars align. BEHAVIOUR (5) is also second up having won at this point of last campaign. Fresh run was sound.
